T1	Participants 262 709	In this study, open-label T3 was administered to 68 high-risk patients undergoing open heart surgery. The New Jersey Risk Assessment was used to calculate the preoperative estimated surgical mortality. A loading dose of T3 was administered: (a) at release of the aortic cross-clamp, (b) whenever the patient became CPB dependent, (c) if the patient exhibited low cardiac output after discontinuing CPB and (d) as pretreatment before initiating CPB
